							<p>
									Origin Youth Group is a group for youngsters in Chinatown from Coalition for a Better Chinese American Community. The group does not own a physical location by itself, but they run from CASL. It started as a way to mobilize youth in Chinatown to promote the power that Chinese Americans hold in society. Darek Lau, Vice President of Origin Youth Group mentioned that currently it is more educational and recreational at the same time. It is a way to relax the members of the group, mentally and physically. This group is different from other youth clubs as it is led by the youth. In general, members of this group are mostly from 14 to 20 years old and have been a part of this group for a long time. These members were initially recruited from their schools. The goal of this group is to provide the youth of Chinatown with a space where they can develop creative thinking, learn how to raise their voices, and talk about issues currently being faced by Chinese community. This group is educating the youth on political topics and in long term, it expects its members to discuss these topics and their thought with their families and in public. Currently, this group is facing funding issues. Lack of funds have limited their recruitment and quality of their workshops. Darek Lau also mentioned that currently due to lack of funds the staff is using the resources accessible to them. In future, they are hoping to get the more funding, so they keep bringing the change in Chinatown community’s youth. 
							</p>
